{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ffe6a075-bfd5-45c2-b940-bdf2824d6e1a","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2** / .NET 9.0. Here's the modern recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private HttpClient _client = null!;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext + synchronous init\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async initialization\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _client = new HttpClient();\n        await _client.GetAsync(\"https://example.com/health\");\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public void Cleanup()\n    {\n        _client.Dispose();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_client);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points for MSTest v3:**\n\n- **`TestContext`** — inject via **constructor parameter** (preferred over the legacy `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property).\n- **Sync init** — use the **constructor** for simple setup.\n- **Async init** — use **`[TestInitialize] async Task`** (async void is not supported).\n- **`[TestCleanup]`** also supports `async Task` if needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0dca841c-a9e4-465a-a7f8-a9db518c356d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In MSTest v3, the recommended way to handle initialization is:\n\n1. **TestContext**: In MSTest v3, `TestContext` can be injected via constructor (this is the modern approach). The old property-based `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` still works but constructor injection is preferred.\n\n2. **Synchronous initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` method or constructor.\n\n3. **Asynchronous initialization**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with an `async Task` return type (supported in MSTest v3).\n\n\n4. **Combining both**: You can use constructor injection for synchronous setup and `[TestInitialize] async Task` for asynchronous initialization in the same test class.","outputTokens":636,"requestId":"7C11:152429:28846A2:2CE1419:69F94883"},"id":"4dd7d189-5444-45e1-8653-af6719733ec7","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:31:59.629Z","parentId":"d89d48d6-5dbb-46a9-b1b0-a1e3192e1197"}
